<BLOCK0><TI>SCHEDULE 4 (<EM>Section 4</EM>) NOTICE OF APPEAL (INFORMAL PROCEDURE)</TI>
<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>NOTICE OF APPEAL</UNDER></TI>
<P>TAKE NOTICE THAT <EM>1526818 Ontario Inc BN:8539874444RC0001, Younan Mikhail</EM> [#omitted]<EM>and Hellen Mikhail</EM> [#omitted]appeals to the Court from assessment of taxation years ending October 31, 2010 to 2013 and taxation years 2010 and 2011 for Younan Mikhail and taxation years 2012 and 2013 for Hellen Mikhail.
<P1>A. Reasons for the appeal. The company was assessed for incentives received in the above years that were not declared as income. In addition however the employees that received the incentives were also assessed for the same amounts resulting in double taxation. In addition on further review with the employees, the amounts indicated are not correct. In particular the large amounts in 2010 were not received. They only remember receiving amounts under $1,000.</P1></P>
<P>B. Statement of relevant facts in support of the appeal. In the case of <CASEREF><SOC>Chopp v. The Queen</SOC></CASEREF>, Mojan J. stated the following: If a shareholder is also an employee of the corporation and receives a benefit in his capacity as employee. the value of that benefit would be taxed under paragraph 6(1)(a) of the act. A corporation is ordinarily permitted to deduct as a business expense the cost of a benefit received or enjoyed by an employee.</P>
<P>I ELECT to have the informal procedure provided by sections 18.1 to 18.28 of the <EM>Tax Court of Canada Act</EM> apply to this appeal.</P>
<P>DATE: February 12, 2018</P>
<P>TO:
<LINE>The Registrar</LINE>
<LINE>Tax Court of Canada</LINE>
<LINE>200 Kent Street</LINE>
<LINE>Ottawa, Ontario</LINE>
<LINE>K1A 0M1</LINE></P>
<P><EM>Correspondence should be addressed to Angelo Carere 2 Chatterson Drive, Ancaster, ON L9G 3X2</EM></P>
<P><EM>905 517-3190</EM></P>
<P>NOTE that if the aggregate of all amounts in issue exceeds <BOLD><UNDER>$25,000</UNDER></BOLD> or the amount of loss in issue exceeds <BOLD><UNDER>$50,000</UNDER></BOLD> and you wish to proceed under the informal procedure, you must use Schedule 17(2).</P></BLOCK1></BLOCK0>
