<BLOCK1><TI>REPLY TO THE NOTICE OF APPEAL</TI>
<P>In reply to the Notice of Appeal with respect to the 2012 and 2013 taxation years, the Attorney General of Canada (the &ldquo;Attorney General&rdquo;) says:</P>
<BLOCK2><N>A.</N><TI>STATEMENT OF FACTS</TI>
<P><P1>1. With respect to the facts alleged in the Notice of Appeal, the Attorney General:
<P2>a. states that except as expressly admitted herein, the Attorney General does not admit any allegation of fact contained in the Notice of Appeal;</P2>
<P2>b. admits the 1526818 Ontario Inc. (&ldquo;Queenslake Pharmacy&rdquo;) was reassessed to include unreported rebates and incentives of $6,078, $4,871, $8,744, $4,480 in the taxation years ended October 31, 2010, October 31, 2011, October 31, 2012, and October 31, 2013;</P2>
<P2>c. admits that the Appellant was assessed benefits conferred by Queenslake Pharmacy of $9,952 and $2,525 in the 2012 and 2013 calendar years, respectively;</P2>
<P2>d. admits the authenticity of the the letter from the Canada Revenue Agency (&ldquo;CRA&rdquo;) to Angelo Carere dated December 12, 2017 and states that the document speaks for itself;</P2>
<P2>e. states that the chart dated March 19, 2018 attached to the Notice of Appeal was submitted by way of evidence and improperly attached: and</P2>
<P2>f. states that the remainder of the Notice of Appeal constitutes argument or advances the relief sought, and denies any facts incidentally alleged and holds the Appellant to the strict proof thereof.</P2></P1></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>B.</N><TI>REPORTING AND ASSESSING HISTORY</TI>
