<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Ratmono (Joe) Thejo, of the City of Toronto, in the Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:</P>
<P>1. I am employed as an officer of the Canada Revenue Agency (the &ldquo;Agency&rdquo;) in the Toronto Centre Tax Services Office. As such, I have personal knowledge of the matters to which I hereinafter depose except for what is stated to be on based on information and belief, and where so stated, I believe to be true.</P>
<P>2. I have charge of the appropriate records of the Agency and have knowledge of the practices of the Agency.</P>
<P>3. I have knowledge of the facts of the Notice of Appeal (the &ldquo;Appeal&rdquo;) filed by the Appellant on April 27, 2018, in respect of the taxation year ended October 31, 2013.</P>
<P>4. My examination of the Agency's records shows that:
<P1>a) on March 16, 2016, the Minister of National Revenue (the &ldquo;Minister&rdquo;) issued a notice that nil tax, interest and penalties was payable for the taxation year ended October 31, 2013.
<P2>Attached to this affidavit and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the Notice of Assessment (the &ldquo;Assessment&rdquo;) for the taxation year ended October 31, 2013, showing the date on which the notice was issued; and</P2></P1>
<P1>b) the Appellant had no taxes, interest, or penalties payable for the taxation year ended October 31, 2013, as detailed on page 1 of the Assessment.</P1></P>
<P>5. I make this affidavit on behalf of the Respondent for an order quashing the Appeal for the taxation year ended October 31, 2013.</P>
